{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d3a411ff-4f06-43a5-ab0b-81bb76bb5898","content":"Here's your complete migration plan from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP):\n\n---\n\n## Migration Plan: VSTest → Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### Phase 1 — Update Package References (per test project)\n\nReplace in each `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- REMOVE -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestFramework\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestAdapter\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.13.0\" />\n\n<!-- ADD -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n```\n\nThe unified `MSTest` package (≥3.2) includes the test framework, adapter, **and** MTP runner.\n\n### Phase 2 — Enable Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\nAdd to each test `.csproj` (or a `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis makes each test project a self-contained executable using MTP instead of `vstest.console`.\n\n### Phase 3 — TRX Reporting\n\nAdd the TRX report extension:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />\n```\n\nAt the CLI, results are produced with:\n```bash\ndotnet test --results-directory ./TestResults -- --report-trx\n```\n\n### Phase 4 — Code Coverage\n\nAdd:\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.13.0\" />\n```\n\nRun with:\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura\n```\n\n### Phase 5 — Azure DevOps Pipeline Changes\n\nReplace the `VSTest@3` task with `DotNetCoreCLI@2`:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      -- --report-trx --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Phase 6 — Validate\n\n1. `dotnet build` all 5 projects — each should produce an `.exe`\n2. `dotnet test` — confirm tests run and TRX + coverage files are emitted\n3. Run pipeline on a feature branch before merging\n\n### Key Notes\n\n| Concern | Detail |\n|---------|--------|\n| **`dotnet test` compat** | Still works; MTP hosts itself inside `dotnet test` |\n| **VS Test Explorer** | Fully supported with MSTest ≥3.2 + MTP |\n| **Parallel projects** | `dotnet test` parallelises projects; within-project parallelism uses `[Parallelize]` as before |\n| **Filter syntax** | Use `--filter` as before, or native `--test-filter` with MTP |\n| **Rollback** | Remove `EnableMSTestRunner`/`OutputType`, restore old packages |\n\nMigrate one project first to validate, then apply to the remaining four via `Directory.Build.props`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b7492974-482c-42bf-95df-2acf746667a4","outputTokens":901,"requestId":"BD01:39A6CA:1D744E1:2136D7D:6A07C708"},"id":"91c408fb-a08a-452e-8ce0-114e97ec31e0","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:23:36.796Z","parentId":"bc13ab29-d9b1-419c-8002-561f75928f51"}
